cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "BOXBOX: Evaluating Large Language Models on Sequential Race-Strategy Decisions"
abstract: >
  A contamination-resistant benchmark that evaluates frontier language models on
  Formula 1 pit-strategy decisions. Decision points are extracted mechanically from
  eleven real races (2024–2026) and scored against an ex-ante optimum from a
  calibrated race simulator.
authors:
